The area Super Ten volleyball teams, through matches played Tuesday, Oct. 20: 
1. WEST DELAWARE — 44-2 overall, 7-0 Wamac East (1st), Wamac tournament champion 
2. CEDAR RAPIDS PRAIRIE — 30-7 overall, 5-1 MVC Mississippi (T-1st), MVC tournament runner-up 
3. CEDAR RAPIDS KENNEDY — 27-9 overall, 6-0 MVC Valley (1st), MVC tournament semifinalist 
4. LINN-MAR — 27-8 overall, 4-2 MVC Valley (3rd), MVC tournament semifinalist 
5. IOWA CITY WEST — 25-11 overall, 3-3 MVC Valley (4th), MVC tournament quarterfinalist 
6. MARION — 28-8 overall, 7-0 Wamac West (1st), Wamac tournament runner-up 
7. WEST BRANCH — 32-5 overall, 6-0 River Valley South (1st), RVC tournament runner-up 
8. WEST LIBERTY — 32-4 overall, 5-1 River Valley South (2nd), RVC tournament champion 
9. CENTER POINT-URBANA — 28-7 overall, 6-1 Wamac West (2nd), Wamac tournament quarterfinalist 
10. WESTERN DUBUQUE — 21-12 overall, 6-1 Wamac East (2nd), Wamac tournament semifinalist 
Area rankings by class: 
Class 5A — 1. C.R. Prairie (30-7), 2. C.R. Kennedy (27-9), 3. Linn-Mar (27-8), 4. Iowa City West (25-11), 5. Iowa City High (16-14). 
Class 4A — 1. West Delaware (44-2), 2. Marion (28-8), 3. Western Dubuque (21-12), 4. Clear Creek Amana (23-16), 5. Independence (20-14). 
Class 3A — 1. West Liberty (32-4), 2. Center Point-Urbana (28-7), 3. Mount Vernon (23-12), 4. Union (23-13), 5. Cascade (18-14). 
Class 2A — 1. West Branch (32-5), 2. North Cedar (28-10), 3. Tipton (21-12), 4. Starmont (30-9), 5. Jesup (16-15). 
Class 1A — 1. Springville (28-7), 2. Turkey Valley (26-6), 3. Iowa Valley (23-8), 4. Montezuma (21-7), 5. Lone Tree (16-10).
